            <title><![CDATA[Customize you Linux/Unix terminal!]]></title>
            <link>https://techharvesting.in/blog/customize-linux-unix-terminal</link>
            <guid>customize-linux-unix-terminal</guid>
            <pubDate>Fri, 11 Feb 2022 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Customize your Terminal in Linux/Macos/WSL without ohmyzsh!]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="customize-your-terminal-in-linuxmacoswsl-without-ohmyzsh">Customize your Terminal in Linux/Macos/WSL without ohmyzsh!<a class="hash-link" href="#customize-your-terminal-in-linuxmacoswsl-without-ohmyzsh" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><h1>Lets make that ugly terminal look better! üêö</h1><p>(I am Doing this on a Raspberrypi, but this can be done on Any Linux Distro, MacOS or Windows Subsystem for Linux if you are on windows)</p><h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="before">Before:<a class="hash-link" href="#before" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h3><p><img src="https://cdn.hashnode.com/res/hashnode/image/upload/v1627456831336/OqBwd6Bby.png" alt="image.png"></p><h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="after">After:<a class="hash-link" href="#after" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h3><p><img src="https://cdn.hashnode.com/res/hashnode/image/upload/v1627456846734/pF83r0fmr.png" alt="image.png"></p><p>If you have watched any other tutorials/posts like this, you know, that we use a package called <code>ohmyzsh</code>, but that slows down the shell a bit, so we will do it without <code>ohmyzsh</code>! Just normal <code>zsh</code>! (We will use a theme called <code>powerlevel10k</code>)</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="step-1-install-zsh">Step 1: Install <code>zsh</code><a class="hash-link" href="#step-1-install-zsh" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><p>Now, most of Linux distributions come Pre Installed with <code>bash</code>, which is a shell, but we will use <code>zsh</code> in this tutorial <br> <br>
So to install zsh on <code>Ubuntu/Debian/Raspbian/Mint/Pop/Any debian based distro</code> run: </p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">sudo</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">apt</span><span class="token plain"> update</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain"></span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">sudo</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">apt</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">install</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">zsh</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>Next run <code>zsh</code> on the command line to test if the installation worked
If it did, you are ready for the next step üéä
else <em>troubleshoot</em> the install üòï</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="step-2-changing-the-default-shell">Step 2: Changing the default shell<a class="hash-link" href="#step-2-changing-the-default-shell" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><p>Open up a new terminal and Bash will popup...
Let us make <code>zsh</code> the default üòé</p><p>To Change the default shell, run: </p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">chsh</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>and when prompted, enter <code>/bin/zsh</code> as the shell</p><p>Now, open a new session, and boom there is <code>zsh</code>... still ugly though</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="step-3-style-it-up-">Step 3: Style it up ü§©<a class="hash-link" href="#step-3-style-it-up-" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="let-us-now-install-our-theme-powerlevel10k">Let us now install our theme <code>powerlevel10k</code><a class="hash-link" href="#let-us-now-install-our-theme-powerlevel10k" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h3><p>First you can install a recomended font... mostly a <code>nerd font</code> (Link to repo below) I use a font called <code>VictorMono NF</code> (also linked below)</p><p>Run: </p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">git</span><span class="token plain"> clone --depth</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">=</span><span class="token number" style="color:rgb(247, 140, 108)">1</span><span class="token plain"> https://github.com/romkatv/powerlevel10k.git ~/powerlevel10k</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain"></span><span class="token builtin class-name" style="color:rgb(255, 203, 139)">echo</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">'source ~/powerlevel10k/powerlevel10k.zsh-theme'</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">&gt;&gt;</span><span class="token plain">~/.zshrc</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>This installs <code>powerlevel10k</code>, When you open up a new session, you get a config wizard: </p><p><img src="https://cdn.hashnode.com/res/hashnode/image/upload/v1627459246091/JU7CQPh7b.png" alt="image.png"></p><p>Answer the question to your liking and then use your new <strong>better</strong> terminal!</p><p><strong>And we did not use Ohmyzsh</strong></p><p>So how did you do it?
Do share your new shell look in the comments below! </p><p>Also <strong>üëç</strong> this post if you found this <em>helpful</em></p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="if-you-really-want-to-use--oh-my-zsh-then-watch-my-video-on-doing-so">If you really want to use  <code>oh-my-zsh</code>, then watch my video on doing so!<a class="hash-link" href="#if-you-really-want-to-use--oh-my-zsh-then-watch-my-video-on-doing-so" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><iframe src="http://youtube.com/embed/ZDghjjwhzVs" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0"></iframe><h1>Links in this post üåê</h1><p><a href="https://gist.github.com/NaseelNiyas/505dba153890058f7e268ae4b9f8a71e" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">My <code>~/.p10k.zsh</code> file copy&amp;paste if you want the same thing üòÑ</a></p><p> <a href="https://github.com/romkatv/powerlevel10k" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Powerlevel10k repo</a> </p><p> <a href="https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Nerd Fonts Repo</a> </p><p><a href="https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts/tree/master/patched-fonts/VictorMono" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Victor Mono NF</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
            <category>terminal</category>
            <category>linux</category>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Setup tailwindcss with nextjs]]></title>
            <link>https://techharvesting.in/blog/nextjs-tailwindcss</link>
            <guid>nextjs-tailwindcss</guid>
            <pubDate>Fri, 11 Feb 2022 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Setup Tailwind CSS with Next.js]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="setup-tailwind-css-with-nextjs">Setup Tailwind CSS with Next.js<a class="hash-link" href="#setup-tailwind-css-with-nextjs" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><p><img src="https://cdn.hashnode.com/res/hashnode/image/upload/v1632979765809/HTEigfQR-.png" alt="image.png"></p><blockquote><p>Tailwind css is Super Awesome. It is my favorite CSS Framework.
This post is all about setting it up with Next.js (My Favorite JavaScript framework)</p></blockquote><h1>The Shorter way</h1><p>If you have not yet created a next.js project, then use this command to set it up with tailwind preconfigured for you!</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">npx create-next-app -e with-tailwindcss next-tailwind</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>Then Change your directory:</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token builtin class-name" style="color:rgb(255, 203, 139)">cd</span><span class="token plain"> next-tailwind</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>And start the server:</p><div class="tabs-container"><ul role="tablist" aria-orientation="horizontal" class="tabs"><li role="tab" tabindex="0" aria-selected="true" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD tabs__item--active">npm</li><li role="tab" tabindex="-1" aria-selected="false" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD">Yarn</li></ul><div class="margin-vert--md"><div role="tabpanel"><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">npm</span><span class="token plain"> run dev</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" hidden=""><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">yarn</span><span class="token plain"> run dev</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div></div></div><h1>The Second Approach</h1><p>If you have already got a project, it still is simple!</p><p>First install a <em>few</em> dependencies:</p><div class="tabs-container"><ul role="tablist" aria-orientation="horizontal" class="tabs"><li role="tab" tabindex="0" aria-selected="true" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD tabs__item--active">npm</li><li role="tab" tabindex="-1" aria-selected="false" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD">Yarn</li></ul><div class="margin-vert--md"><div role="tabpanel"><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">npm</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">install</span><span class="token plain"> -D tailwindcss@latest postcss@latest autoprefixer@latest</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" hidden=""><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">yarn</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">add</span><span class="token plain"> -D tailwindcss@latest postcss@latest autoprefixer@latest</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div></div></div><p>This should install tailwind, postcss and autoprefixer</p><p>Next, Get generate your configuration for Tailwind and Postcss.</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">npx tailwindcss init -p</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>Then, import it in your <code>pages/_app.js</code> file</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-jsx theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx jsx"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-jsx codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token keyword" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">import</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">'tailwindcss/tailwind.css'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">;</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>Finally, Run your server</p><div class="tabs-container"><ul role="tablist" aria-orientation="horizontal" class="tabs"><li role="tab" tabindex="0" aria-selected="true" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD tabs__item--active">npm</li><li role="tab" tabindex="-1" aria-selected="false" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD">Yarn</li></ul><div class="margin-vert--md"><div role="tabpanel"><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">npm</span><span class="token plain"> run dev</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" hidden=""><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">yarn</span><span class="token plain"> run dev</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div></div></div><p>That was all you needed to do to have tailwind in your project. If you apply a class now, it will reflect on the webpage.</p><h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="links">Links<a class="hash-link" href="#links" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h3><p><a href="https://tailwindcss.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tailwind CSS</a>
<a href="https://nextjs.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Next.js</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
            <category>nextjs</category>
            <category>tailwindcss</category>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[The best Nextjs Workflow]]></title>
            <link>https://techharvesting.in/blog/nextjs-workflow</link>
            <guid>nextjs-workflow</guid>
            <pubDate>Fri, 11 Feb 2022 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[The best next.js workflow with Typescript, sass and more!]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="the-best-nextjs-workflow-with-typescript-sass-and-more">The best next.js workflow with Typescript, sass and more!<a class="hash-link" href="#the-best-nextjs-workflow-with-typescript-sass-and-more" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><p> Do you use Next.js? then make sure you use these tools to boost your productivity and development experience!</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="typescript">Typescript<a class="hash-link" href="#typescript" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><p><img src="https://cdn.hashnode.com/res/hashnode/image/upload/v1631503196236/-nmurDa0s.png" alt="ts.png"></p><blockquote><p>Typescript is a very popular and good choice for using with Next.js or any other framework ! It is going to reduce the amount of errors we get by introducing a type system with JavaScript</p></blockquote><p>To Create a Next.js project with <strong>typescript</strong> , run:</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">npx create-next-app next-typescript-app --ts</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>This will create a next.js project with typescript support and also a <code>tsconfig.json</code> file (the <strong>typescript configuration</strong> file)</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="sass">Sass<a class="hash-link" href="#sass" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><p><img src="https://cdn.hashnode.com/res/hashnode/image/upload/v1631503254762/Tvmhj-xYd.png" alt="sass.png"></p><blockquote><p><strong>Sass</strong> is an awesome superset for css which supports a lot of features like nesting , <code>if</code> conditions and more. You can learn more about sass <a href="https://sass-lang.com/documentation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a> </p></blockquote><p>It is very simple to add <code>sass</code> to your project if you use next.js. Just add sass with</p><div class="tabs-container"><ul role="tablist" aria-orientation="horizontal" class="tabs"><li role="tab" tabindex="0" aria-selected="true" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD tabs__item--active">npm</li><li role="tab" tabindex="-1" aria-selected="false" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD">Yarn</li></ul><div class="margin-vert--md"><div role="tabpanel"><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">npm</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">install</span><span class="token plain"> sass</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" hidden=""><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">yarn</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">add</span><span class="token plain"> sass</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div></div></div><p>Then rename your <code>.css</code> files with <code>.scss</code> or <code>.sass</code> extensions. If you use the <code>.sass</code> extension, when you will have to <strong>remove</strong> the curly braces and the semicolons. Or you can use the <code>.scss</code> extension. You can also rename the css module files with the <code>.sass</code> or the <code>.scss</code> extension</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="prettier">Prettier<a class="hash-link" href="#prettier" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><p><img src="https://cdn.hashnode.com/res/hashnode/image/upload/v1631504232931/aSwstYs-C.png" alt="prettier.png"></p><blockquote><p>Does your code not get formatted the way you want? use Prettier! prettier is a code formatter which is also very popular you can learn more about prettier  <a href="https://prettier.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a> </p></blockquote><p>To add prettier to your project, run:</p><div class="tabs-container"><ul role="tablist" aria-orientation="horizontal" class="tabs"><li role="tab" tabindex="0" aria-selected="true" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD tabs__item--active">npm</li><li role="tab" tabindex="-1" aria-selected="false" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD">Yarn</li></ul><div class="margin-vert--md"><div role="tabpanel"><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">npm</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">install</span><span class="token plain"> prettier -D</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" hidden=""><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">yarn</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">add</span><span class="token plain"> prettier -D</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div></div></div><p>I also create a npm script in my <code>package.json</code> to format my code. ( I named it <em>clean</em>)</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-json theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx json"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-json codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"scripts"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">{</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">    </span><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"dev"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">"next dev"</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">    </span><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"build"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">"next build"</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">    </span><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"start"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">"next start"</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">    </span><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"lint"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">"next lint"</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">    </span><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"clean"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">"prettier --write ."</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">}</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>So now when you run <code>npm run clean</code> of <code>yarn clean</code> you will see that your code gets clean. I also create a <code>.prettierrc</code> file in the root of my project and give the following in it:</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-json theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx json"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-json codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">{</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"singleQuote"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token boolean" style="color:rgb(255, 88, 116)">true</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain"></span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">}</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>But if you look carefully, then you will find you that it also format the files in our <code>.next</code> folder created by next.js, so to <em>ignore</em> the files in the <code>.next</code> folder, create a <code>.prettierignore</code> file at the root of your project with the following contents</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-sh theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx sh"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-sh codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain"># next.js dev server files</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">.next/</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain"># npm packages</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">node_modules/</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="using-husky-to-format-code">Using husky to format code<a class="hash-link" href="#using-husky-to-format-code" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><center><h1><font size="100">üê∂</font></h1></center><p>I did not find a logo for husky ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è</p><blockquote><p>If you use git, this will be super useful! you can create a git hook, which will format our code before each commit.</p></blockquote><p>Since we have prettier already installed, run:</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-sh theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx sh"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-sh codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">npx mrm@2 lint-staged</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>We are also using husky in here. so it will create a <code>.husky</code> folder</p><p>And in our <code>package.json</code>, in the <code>lint-staged</code> section, change to the following if using typescript</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-json theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx json"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-json codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"lint-staged"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">{</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">    </span><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"*.ts"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">"eslint --cache --fix"</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">    </span><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"*.{tsx,.ts,css,md}"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">"prettier --write"</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(199, 146, 234)">}</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>Now, I did a quick commit with</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">git</span><span class="token plain"> commit -m </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">'ü¶ã Formatting with Prettier'</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>and.....   Our code is pretty as we specified in our <code>.prettierrc</code> file</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="testing-">Testing üß™<a class="hash-link" href="#testing-" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><p><img src="https://cdn.hashnode.com/res/hashnode/image/upload/v1631506691302/XW4sUx0Pw.png" alt="image.png"></p><blockquote><p>If you want to test your next.js application, use <code>cypress</code> as shown in the next.js  <a href="https://nextjs.org/docs/testing" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">docs</a> </p></blockquote><p>Install cypress by running:</p><div class="tabs-container"><ul role="tablist" aria-orientation="horizontal" class="tabs"><li role="tab" tabindex="0" aria-selected="true" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD tabs__item--active">npm</li><li role="tab" tabindex="-1" aria-selected="false" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD">Yarn</li></ul><div class="margin-vert--md"><div role="tabpanel"><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">npm</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">install</span><span class="token plain"> -D cypress</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" hidden=""><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">yarn</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">add</span><span class="token plain"> -D cypress</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div></div></div><div class="admonition admonition-tip alert alert--success"><div class="admonition-heading"><h5><span class="admonition-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="12" height="16" viewBox="0 0 12 16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M6.5 0C3.48 0 1 2.19 1 5c0 .92.55 2.25 1 3 1.34 2.25 1.78 2.78 2 4v1h5v-1c.22-1.22.66-1.75 2-4 .45-.75 1-2.08 1-3 0-2.81-2.48-5-5.5-5zm3.64 7.48c-.25.44-.47.8-.67 1.11-.86 1.41-1.25 2.06-1.45 3.23-.02.05-.02.11-.02.17H5c0-.06 0-.13-.02-.17-.2-1.17-.59-1.83-1.45-3.23-.2-.31-.42-.67-.67-1.11C2.44 6.78 2 5.65 2 5c0-2.2 2.02-4 4.5-4 1.22 0 2.36.42 3.22 1.19C10.55 2.94 11 3.94 11 5c0 .66-.44 1.78-.86 2.48zM4 14h5c-.23 1.14-1.3 2-2.5 2s-2.27-.86-2.5-2z"></path></svg></span>tip</h5></div><div class="admonition-content"><p>Cypress is used for <strong>end to end testing</strong> of your next.js application.</p></div></div><p>Create a cypress script</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-json theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx json"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-json codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token property" style="color:rgb(128, 203, 196)">"test"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:rgb(127, 219, 202)">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(173, 219, 103)">"cypress open"</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>Run cypress with</p><div class="tabs-container"><ul role="tablist" aria-orientation="horizontal" class="tabs"><li role="tab" tabindex="0" aria-selected="true" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD tabs__item--active">npm</li><li role="tab" tabindex="-1" aria-selected="false" class="tabs__item tabItem_LplD">Yarn</li></ul><div class="margin-vert--md"><div role="tabpanel"><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">npm</span><span class="token plain"> run </span><span class="token builtin class-name" style="color:rgb(255, 203, 139)">test</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" hidden=""><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#d6deeb"><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(130, 170, 255)">yarn</span><span class="token plain"> run </span><span class="token builtin class-name" style="color:rgb(255, 203, 139)">test</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></div></div></div><p>You can create your tests now ( I am not showing anything now). You can learn more  <a href="https://nextjs.org/docs/testing" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a> </p><p>That was it! You can of course add on to this list...
